text: After reading a few comments I see that there's not so much guys anymore who enjoy 80's and 90's style action movies. Ok, yeah, obviously these kind of movies are little dumb, with one-liners, explosions, fighting, no drama, weak storyline, etc. But that's the part of a genre! Seems like these days all we need is some lame ass comedies with beautiful Channing or CGI movies with pretty Chris.I have grown with classic action movies like Cobra, Tango&Cash, Rambo, Terminator, Showdown in the Little Tokyo and more and I can't accept weak pretty boy CGI movies that we all are begining to love. There's no heart in those movies. Ok, old-school action movies are violent, but there's so much heart and so much work behind the scenes, training and talent! These guys are legends! Maybe younger guys don't get me because they don't remember those awesome times when Sly and Arnie movies was a big deal. For me, this still is really big deal, that's why I love this franchise!

I realise the world was goin' all sissy with the movies and when Sly stepped up and decided to inject some balls onto the silver screen all the washed-ups (not their fault, just that world has gone soft) decided to jump on the bandwagon. Man, it shoulda been my idea! It shoulda been Milla Jovovich in this one rather than that girl there.  I never watched 2, I figure its like the Matrix, One summed up everything and what next could it be? But, I need to see this one - Wesley Snipes, Mel Gibson (seen every single one of his movies) Banderas, Ford, Dolph Lundgren (seen every single one of his movies), need to see more Jet Li whoopassing and when will we see Stephen Segal bustin asses? Nah man, das like, like, I mean that's like Testosterone Nirvana right there, man - an ode to masculinity and action and sweat, and hairy chests and braun and explosions and guns and smoke and awesome badasses and machines and did I say guns and explosions. text: Â  We live in an era where even something that should be a relaxation, such as watching a movie, became something that's more of a burden than anything else. People need to realise this particular franchise is made for the sake of it, not to live up to the expectations of some scumbags who watch movies just to see where they'll find something bad in them orÂ where they'll find a mistake. This franchise is made for people who appreciate the ''movie'' for what it stands for - funÂ and for nostalgic people. To insure that, it uses the forever-expanding ''golden age of pop culture'' movie legends, a normal plot which is made the way it is to give the audienceÂ luxury to focus more on all those legends sharing screen time together rather than the plot itself. It's not meant to be a mind bending, mapped out pacing, unpredictable ''new century'' movie, it's meant to be just the opposite and that's the beauty of it. As long as they're enjoying each other and having fun on set all together, it transfers to the screen. I feel sorry for people who can't see that, but on the other hand, I'm not surprised since we live in a time where is better and/or easier to be fake, artificial and factory-made rather than true..

text: Saw it last week.  Takeaways: 1. Wesley is back like a mo'fo - absolutely loved his reasoning for being locked up (his performance WILL reignite any/all fanboy wishes of Blade reprisals, promise); Â  2. Â Even with the steroids, Sly's knees let you know how old he is...the knees know; 3. Â Harrison Ford is smoothly entrenching himself into "grumpy old man" status - move over Clint. Â His back'n'forth with Statham is awesome - imagine using slang with your grandpa - yeah thats pretty much the reaction Ford gives..like every time lol; 4. Ceasar gets Brutus'ed...you'll see; 5. you'll feel sorry for Arnold...seriously...watch him gingerly saddle up to Sly in the hospital scene...painful to watch; 6. Kellen was actually one of the better...I repeat, BETTER...parts of the entire flic; 7. Ronda Rousy couldn't act her way outta paper bag, and her misaligned jaw is noticeable as shit every time she opens her mouth...but she works the hell outta a red mini...so there's that...; 8. Â Mel seems to be having a bit too much fun as the Big Bad;Â  9. Â Lack of Jackie Chan inclusion is getting old. Â Either in 4 or fuck off; and 10. as a self-admitted action junkie, this is my kinda fix...  If you like 80's era action movies where the hero kills everything moving w/ one gun, a survival knife, a bandoleer full of grenades and never has to reload then this is your shit.

text: This will be my last opinion about this film, The Expendable 3, why it failed. Â Franchise fatigue, offered as the main reason for Expendable 3's failure, really just means the filmmakers tried to fleece the public once too often. Yes, there's one born every minute, but you're supposed to offer something in return â€” entertainment or spectacle â€” when you empty a sucker's wallet. Expendables 3 might be too little too soon, but in all the what-the-hell-happened analysis, the repetitive non-sense plot, the weak screenplay, for a lack of a better word, has ground down to near nothingness and last but not least, watering down the action to get a more family-friendly rating, in other words, the PG rating, are the main factors that made this movie fail.

text: I've been a fan of Stallone since the first Rocky opened in theaters, but some of his recent movies have really tested me on a number of fronts. Bullet to the head was like an updated version of Cobra, except boring. He seem to recover with Escape Plan which I thought was a solid film. But then he just completely dialed in a performance on Grudge Match which looked good on paper but was played by two very tired looking stars. Now this movie comes out... Jesus.  My tolerance level has been admittedly set too high for some of Sly's stuff, but Expendables 3 was THE biggest pile of garbage I have EVER seen him do. He didn't even dial in a performance. He slept walked the whole thing. To call the plot mindless is to give it WAAAAY too much credit. That wasn't even written on the back of a napkin. More like an inscribed notion on road kill. And now he wants to revisit Rambo? He's really burned out his welcome on the whole 80's retro hero front. The man is nearly 70 years old and doing a Rambo movie now? Please Sly... Get yourself grounded.

text: If Hollywood plans to make a "ExpendablesÂ 4". the writers make it where it takes after the events of taking down ConradÂ Stonebanks.Â  Here's my movie idea for the screen writers.  In the same day, as Ross & his friends celebrating, welcome the newÂ members on the team.Â  In that same day in theÂ middle of the afternoon. A woman is having tea & reading a magazine. SeesÂ her daughter swimming in the pool doing her laps to keep herself in shape. As she finishes & exits out of the pool, grabs a towel.Â  She dries herself off and askÂ her motherÂ that she curious of whenÂ Conrad be coming back soon.  Her mother tells her. She hasn't heard from him today.Â  MustÂ beÂ caught up with some more art dealing.Â He gets prettyÂ busy inÂ the business world. Then a man walks toward her who works for them,Â the daughter seesÂ him &Â tellsÂ herÂ mother anÂ unfortunate news.Â Â Â Her mother takes the news shocking & drops her tea cup, itÂ smashes into the ground.Â  shouts out her name.  The daughter runs towards her & holds on to her mother, she cries on her shoulder. SheÂ wonders of what happen, her mother tells her (sobbing) in tears.Â  ConradÂ is not coming home. He's been killed.  HerselfÂ is in shocked,Â Into herÂ eyes a single tear drop. then her eyesÂ filled with anger. She demands to know who killed him.Â Â Weeks later afterÂ they hadÂ a privateÂ funeral for him. SheÂ assumes control of Conrad business. In her private gym in her workout. InÂ her sparring sessionsÂ & keeping her martial arts of Taewondo.Â  She beats the hell out of her spar partners.  One of her employees isÂ walking to her gym with a briefcase. As she gets ready for another sparring round.Â Â One of her lieutenants tells her. that one of her sources has found the informationÂ she's asked for and theÂ package has arrived. She looks &Â sees him,Â takes off her gloves. walks to him.Â  Then he opensÂ the briefcase & hands her a file from the C.I.A.Â which it containsÂ the profiles of the team & the man who killed Conrad.Â  She looks through it.  Then she puts a price tags on their heads. But she wants Barney Ross alive, so she can kill him for herself.Â  She puts together her own team. They get stateside, while they get resupplied &Â rested.Â  Barney getsÂ visit from Drummer,Â tells himÂ there's a priceÂ on them.Â Â BarneyÂ asked who order it, DrummerÂ gives him a file of a young woman that has taken over Conrad business & continuingÂ selling, trading black arms dealing.Â Â Â Barney looks at the pics of her & see her name.Â  "Alektra Stonebanks" she isÂ Conrad's daughter.Â Â  She's out for revenge. text: Mel Gibson was the best thing in this movie. Among the problems this film had, there was little to no humor/fun in it, because Stallone takes himself too seriously. At least Mel and Antonio Banderas were the only ones who looked like they were having fun with their roles. We don't go into an Expendables movie to see these young morons that we don't care about! We wanna see the older, veteran badasses! And directors need to stop giving roles to that IDIOT Kellan Lutz. Seriously, that talentless asshole literally pollutes EVERYTHING he touches. STOP GIVING THAT CLOWN WORK!! Ronda Rousey could've played an actual character, but instead she's just a role--the token female member whose only function is to rebuff the frat-guys who try to hit on her and say "Men...". The main cast--Jason Statham, Jet Li, Dolph Lundgren, Randy Couture and Terry Crews--are completely shafted into the background; Wesley Snipes has all of about 5 minutes of screen time, and you completely forget that Arnold is in it, somewhere back there in the corner. Look Sly, we love you, but you're not Robert DeNiro. Stop expecting us to take you seriously and treat you like him! Stick to what you do best, and we'll watch you. PS: If there's a 4th installment, no young dumbass recruits please. Stick with your real team.

text: The Expendables 4â€™ Release Date Locked In For August 2015: A Much Bigger Mixing of International Action Stars Expected On The Upcoming Film!  Oct 03, 2014 11:06 PM EDT Tagsthe expendables 4, expendables, Jackie Chan, steven seagul, sylvester stallone The Expendables 4 is a sequel of the movie Expendables, which started on 2010, directed by Avi Lerner. Starred by the legendary Sylvester Stallone, as Barney Ross, the movie already got its audiences for the past sequels. The story started when the Expendables are committed of treason after the Presidential plane explodes. They become fugitives and are hunted by the FBI and two bounty hunters. The group employ the help of Trench to find the real culprit. And when he is discovered, so are his connections to Barney Ross. The Expendables are eventually caught and arrested, and Trench forms the New Expendables, with some familiar faces, to break them out. The film ends with the team disbanding, moving on to different lives. ADVERTISING Like Us on Facebook Â Â   Expendables members are casts with Jason Statham as Lee Christmas, Antonio Banderas as Galgo, Jet-Li as Yin Yang, Wesley Snipes as Doc, Bruce Willis as Church, Dolph Lundgrenas Gunner Jensen, Marlon Brando as Billy Drummer, Terry Crews as Hale Caesar, Randy Couture as Toll Road, Kellan Lutz as John Smilee, Ronda Rousev as Luna, Glen Powell as Thorn, Victor Ortiz as Mars and Arnold Schwarzenegger as Trench Mauser. Some of the biggest names in action films will also be shooting for Expendables 4, like, Denzel Washington as the President, Kevin Costner as Commisioner Jones, FBI Officer, Mark Wahlberg as Lieutenant Williamson, FBI Officer, Ian McKellen as John Christmas, Lee's father, Ray Park as Speed and Dave Bautista as Beast, bodyguards of Artemis Wilson, Hugh Jackman as Holt Bartenbauzer and Vin Diesel as Frank Walker, bounty hunters, Ron Perlman as Artemis Wilson, former James Bond, Pierce Brosnan, Hulk Hogan, Robert de Niro, Steven Seagal, Harrison Ford as Max Drummer and the main villain Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson. While the New Expendables are filled by Scarlett Johanson as Jamie Wilson, mother of Kellan Ross and wife of Artemis Wilson, Aaron Taylor-Johnson as Kellan Ross, Barney's son, Chuck Norris as Booker, Clint Eastwood as McCain, Mickey Rourke as Tool, Liam Neeson as Hunter, Tom Cruise as Maverick, Nicolas Cage as Ryder and Jackie Chan as Wong. In an interview with Den of Geek, Chan explained his disappearance on the movie's third sequel, "This morning I did hear - the office called - Sly [Stallone] wants me for 'Expendables 4.' I said, 'Okay.' Because they already asked me to be in two and three, but I refused. Well, I didn't refuse, but I said, 'Sly, can't we just do you and me? Not just a bunch of people and me only coming out for five minutes.' Because then the audience is, 'Oh!' And then I'm gone." According to Stallone, they plan on adding more celebrities from around the world and not just Americans. The star cast will be international and hence appeal to a global audience at a personal level. "We always wanted to work with Jackie, but due to a shortage of central roles, an arrangement could not be made. However, in the upcoming installment, we will surely try to bring him on board. For The Expendables 4, we are trying to reduce the number of stars and increase their individual screen time. Let's see how that goes!" Stallone said. Besides the leak of Expendables 3 before its arrival on theaters in August 2015, many are still wanting to see more on The Expendables 4.
author: Sasa Mrdj
